	abstract = {Decision science, by combining techniques like Generative Intelligence and Retrieval-Augmented Generation, System Dynamics, and Strategy Mapping with the Balanced Scorecard, can become a powerful tool for businesses to not only make informed decisions but also gain a deeper understanding of their resources as identified by the Resource-Based View of the Firm. The understanding can become quantitative by creating either a higher-level System Dynamics model or a detailed Digital Twin. Either way, this integrated approach fosters a more comprehensive picture of a company’s assets and capabilities and enables a more sophisticated and effective formulation of the company strategy. Finally, the principles and techniques of the Balanced Scorecard can be adapted based on the capabilities of modern AI systems to maintain a tighter control on strategy implementation. © The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG 2025.},
