	abstract = {In this paper, it is described how LLMs can be used to extract knowledge from large number of geological papers and books and provide fast access to certain petrophysical parameters and depositional environment information that can be required during reservoir evaluation and modeling. The approach for knowledge extraction without requirement for extensive and computationally expensive fine-tuning is presented and explained. Then comparison of model outputs with and without knowledge databased access is provided to confirm in qualitative and quantitative manner capabilities of proposed framework. At conclusion part it will be discussed how proposed tool can bring value to existing O&G business processes along with how it can be extended in the future research. © 4th EAGE Digitalization Conference and Exhibition 2024.},
